{
  "video_id": "XY_lzonfE3I",
  "title": "A new way to remove CO2 from the atmosphere | Jennifer Wilcox",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13870.0,
      "end_time": 15421.0,
      "text": "Four hundred parts per million:"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15445.0,
      "end_time": 20233.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s the approximate concentration of CO2 in the air today."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 20257.0,
      "end_time": 21680.0,
      "text": "What does this even mean?"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22830.0,
      "end_time": 25506.0,
      "text": "For every 400 molecules of carbon dioxide,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 25531.0,
      "end_time": 30430.0,
      "text": "we have another million molecules of oxygen and nitrogen."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 30680.0,
      "end_time": 33969.0,
      "text": "In this room today, there are about 1,800 of us."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 33993.0,
      "end_time": 37826.0,
      "text": "Imagine just one of us was wearing a green shirt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 37850.0,
      "end_time": 40664.0,
      "text": "and you&#39;re asked to find that single person."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 41224.0,
      "end_time": 44943.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s the challenge we&#39;re facing when capturing CO2"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 44967.0,
      "end_time": 46545.0,
      "text": "directly out of the air."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 47357.0,
      "end_time": 48783.0,
      "text": "Sounds pretty easy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 48807.0,
      "end_time": 51199.0,
      "text": "pulling CO2 out of the air."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 51223.0,
      "end_time": 52766.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s actually really difficult."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 52790.0,
      "end_time": 54610.0,
      "text": "But I&#39;ll tell you what is easy:"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 54634.0,
      "end_time": 58650.0,
      "text": "avoiding CO2 emissions to begin with."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 58701.0,
      "end_time": 60317.0,
      "text": "But we&#39;re not doing that."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 61289.0,
      "end_time": 65290.0,
      "text": "So now what we have to think about is going back;"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 65313.0,
      "end_time": 68283.0,
      "text": "pulling CO2 back out of the air."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 68663.0,
      "end_time": 72538.0,
      "text": "Even though it&#39;s difficult, it&#39;s actually possible to do this."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 72983.0,
      "end_time": 76552.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;m going to share with you today where this technology is at"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 76576.0,
      "end_time": 79264.0,
      "text": "and where it just may be heading in the near future."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 80106.0,
      "end_time": 84936.0,
      "text": "Now, the earth naturally removes CO2 from the air"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 84960.0,
      "end_time": 89613.0,
      "text": "by seawater, soils, plants and even rocks."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 89637.0,
      "end_time": 94355.0,
      "text": "And although engineers and scientists are doing the invaluable work"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 94379.0,
      "end_time": 97631.0,
      "text": "to accelerate these natural processes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 97655.0,
      "end_time": 99695.0,
      "text": "it simply won&#39;t be enough."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 99719.0,
      "end_time": 102730.0,
      "text": "The good news is, we have more."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 102970.0,
      "end_time": 105911.0,
      "text": "Thanks to human ingenuity, we have the technology today"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 105935.0,
      "end_time": 109223.0,
      "text": "to remove CO2 out of the air"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 109247.0,
      "end_time": 111852.0,
      "text": "using a chemically manufactured approach."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 111876.0,
      "end_time": 115141.0,
      "text": "I like to think of this as a synthetic forest."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 115165.0,
      "end_time": 120485.0,
      "text": "There are two basic approaches to growing or building such a forest."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 120509.0,
      "end_time": 125613.0,
      "text": "One is using CO2-grabbing chemicals dissolved in water."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 125637.0,
      "end_time": 129491.0,
      "text": "Another is using solid materials with CO2-grabbing chemicals."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 129514.00000000001,
      "end_time": 132998.0,
      "text": "No matter which approach you choose, they basically look the same."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 133799.0,
      "end_time": 137592.0,
      "text": "So what I&#39;m showing you here is what a system might look like"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 137616.0,
      "end_time": 139770.0,
      "text": "to do just this."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 139101.0,
      "end_time": 141338.0,
      "text": "This is called an air contactor."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 141362.0,
      "end_time": 143648.0,
      "text": "You can see it has to be really, really wide"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 143672.0,
      "end_time": 145829.0,
      "text": "in order to have a high enough surface area"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 145854.0,
      "end_time": 148570.0,
      "text": "to process all of the air required,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 148594.0,
      "end_time": 149745.0,
      "text": "because remember,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 149770.0,
      "end_time": 153748.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re trying to capture just 400 molecules out of a million."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 154293.0,
      "end_time": 157264.0,
      "text": "Using the liquid-based approach to do this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 157288.0,
      "end_time": 159654.0,
      "text": "you take this high surface area packing material,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 159678.0,
      "end_time": 162499.0,
      "text": "you fill the contactor with the packing material,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 162523.0,
      "end_time": 167195.0,
      "text": "you use pumps to distribute liquid across the packing material,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 167219.0,
      "end_time": 170130.0,
      "text": "and you can use fans, as you can see in the front,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 170154.0,
      "end_time": 172595.0,
      "text": "to bubble the air through the liquid."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 173173.0,
      "end_time": 176985.0,
      "text": "The CO2 in the air is separated from the liquid"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 177900.0,
      "end_time": 183667.0,
      "text": "by reacting with the really strong-binding CO2 molecules in solution."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 183692.0,
      "end_time": 186354.0,
      "text": "And in order to capture a lot of CO2,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 186378.0,
      "end_time": 188946.0,
      "text": "you have to make this contactor deeper."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 189420.0,
      "end_time": 190801.0,
      "text": "But there&#39;s an optimization,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 190825.0,
      "end_time": 192870.0,
      "text": "because the deeper you make that contactor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 192895.0,
      "end_time": 196580.0,
      "text": "the more energy you&#39;re spending on bubbling all that air through."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 197550.0,
      "end_time": 201409.0,
      "text": "So air contactors for direct air capture have this unique characteristic design,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 201433.0,
      "end_time": 205755.0,
      "text": "where they have this huge surface area, but a relatively thin thickness."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 206178.0,
      "end_time": 208805.0,
      "text": "And now once you&#39;ve captured the CO2,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 209527.0,
      "end_time": 213408.0,
      "text": "you have to be able to recycle that material that you used to capture it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 213432.0,
      "end_time": 214970.0,
      "text": "over and over again."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 214995.0,
      "end_time": 217982.0,
      "text": "The scale of carbon capture is so enormous"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 218600.0,
      "end_time": 220214.0,
      "text": "that the capture process must be sustainable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 220238.0,
      "end_time": 222318.0,
      "text": "and you can&#39;t use a material just once."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 222758.0,
      "end_time": 226981.0,
      "text": "And so recycling the material requires an enormous amount of heat,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 227500.0,
      "end_time": 230261.0,
      "text": "because think about it: CO2 is so dilute in the air,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 230285.0,
      "end_time": 233135.0,
      "text": "that material is binding it really strong,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 233159.0,
      "end_time": 236995.0,
      "text": "and so you need a lot of heat in order to recycle the material."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 237407.0,
      "end_time": 240700.0,
      "text": "And to recycle the material with that heat,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 240940.0,
      "end_time": 245887.0,
      "text": "what happens is that concentrated CO2 that you got from dilute CO2 in the air"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 245911.0,
      "end_time": 247504.0,
      "text": "is now released,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 247528.0,
      "end_time": 250100.0,
      "text": "and you produce high-purity CO2."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 250417.0,
      "end_time": 252140.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s really important,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 252164.0,
      "end_time": 256366.0,
      "text": "because high-purity CO2 is easier to liquify,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 256390.0,
      "end_time": 259553.0,
      "text": "easier to transport, whether it&#39;s in a pipeline or a truck,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 259577.0,
      "end_time": 261798.0,
      "text": "or even easier to use directly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 261822.0,
      "end_time": 264411.0,
      "text": "say, as a fuel or a chemical."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 265330.0,
      "end_time": 268811.0,
      "text": "So I want to talk a little bit more about that energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 268835.0,
      "end_time": 273480.0,
      "text": "The heat required to regenerate or recycle these materials"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 273720.0,
      "end_time": 279525.0,
      "text": "absolutely dictates the energy and the subsequent cost of doing this."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 280834.0,
      "end_time": 282762.0,
      "text": "So I ask a question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 282786.0,
      "end_time": 285644.0,
      "text": "How much energy do you think it takes"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 285668.0,
      "end_time": 289409.0,
      "text": "to remove a million tons of CO2 from the air"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 289433.0,
      "end_time": 290791.0,
      "text": "in a given year?"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 291343.0,
      "end_time": 293154.0,
      "text": "The answer is: a power plant."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 293178.0,
      "end_time": 296847.0,
      "text": "It takes a power plant to capture CO2 directly from the air."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 296871.0,
      "end_time": 298755.0,
      "text": "Depending on which approach you choose,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 298779.0,
      "end_time": 303197.0,
      "text": "the power plant could be on the order of 300 to 500 megawatts."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 303847.0,
      "end_time": 307656.0,
      "text": "And you have to be careful about what kind of power plant you choose."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 307680.0,
      "end_time": 309357.0,
      "text": "If you choose coal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 309381.0,
      "end_time": 312958.0,
      "text": "you end up emitting more CO2 than you capture."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 313509.0,
      "end_time": 315332.0,
      "text": "Now let&#39;s talk about costs."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 315356.0,
      "end_time": 318830.0,
      "text": "An energy-intensive version of this technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 318854.0,
      "end_time": 321945.0,
      "text": "could cost you as much as $1,000 a ton"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 321969.0,
      "end_time": 323318.0,
      "text": "just to capture it."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 324183.0,
      "end_time": 325543.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s translate that."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 326128.0,
      "end_time": 330143.0,
      "text": "If you were to take that very expensive CO2 and convert it to a liquid fuel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 330167.0,
      "end_time": 332503.0,
      "text": "that comes out to 50 dollars a gallon."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 333179.0,
      "end_time": 335712.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s way too expensive; it&#39;s not feasible."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 335737.0,
      "end_time": 338148.0,
      "text": "So how could we bring these costs down?"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 338172.0,
      "end_time": 340644.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s, in part, the work that I do."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 341771.0,
      "end_time": 344490.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a company today, a commercial-scale company,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 344514.0,
      "end_time": 347203.0,
      "text": "that can do this as low as 600 dollars a ton."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 347227.0,
      "end_time": 351800.0,
      "text": "There are several other companies that are developing technologies"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 351320.0,
      "end_time": 353157.0,
      "text": "that can do this even cheaper than that."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 353583.0,
      "end_time": 355352.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m going to talk to you a little bit"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 355376.0,
      "end_time": 357349.0,
      "text": "about a few of these different companies."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 357373.0,
      "end_time": 359410.0,
      "text": "One is called Carbon Engineering."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 359650.0,
      "end_time": 360533.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re based out of Canada."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 360557.0,
      "end_time": 363450.0,
      "text": "They use a liquid-based approach for separation"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 363474.0,
      "end_time": 367739.0,
      "text": "combined with burning super-abundant, cheap natural gas"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 367763.0,
      "end_time": 370970.0,
      "text": "to supply the heat required."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 370122.0,
      "end_time": 371806.0,
      "text": "They have a clever approach"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 371830.0,
      "end_time": 376120.0,
      "text": "that allows them to co-capture the CO2 from the air"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 376144.0,
      "end_time": 380103.0,
      "text": "and the CO2 that they generate from burning the natural gas."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 380127.0,
      "end_time": 381929.0,
      "text": "And so by doing this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 381953.0,
      "end_time": 385371.0,
      "text": "they offset excess pollution and they reduce costs."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 386600.0,
      "end_time": 390510.0,
      "text": "Switzerland-based Climeworks and US-based Global Thermostat"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 390760.0,
      "end_time": 391679.0,
      "text": "use a different approach."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 391703.0,
      "end_time": 394311.0,
      "text": "They use solid materials for capture."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 394336.0,
      "end_time": 397119.0,
      "text": "Climeworks uses heat from the earth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 397143.0,
      "end_time": 398556.0,
      "text": "or geothermal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 398580.0,
      "end_time": 401692.0,
      "text": "or even excess steam from other industrial processes"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 401716.0,
      "end_time": 404750.0,
      "text": "to cut down on pollution and costs."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 404759.0,
      "end_time": 406959.0,
      "text": "Global Thermostat takes a different approach."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 406983.0,
      "end_time": 409830.0,
      "text": "They focus on the heat required"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 409854.0,
      "end_time": 413527.0,
      "text": "and the speed in which it moves through the material"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 413551.0,
      "end_time": 418229.0,
      "text": "so that they&#39;re able to release and produce that CO2"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 418254.0,
      "end_time": 420290.0,
      "text": "at a really fast rate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 420530.0,
      "end_time": 423408.0,
      "text": "which allows them to have a more compact design"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 423432.0,
      "end_time": 425433.0,
      "text": "and overall cheaper costs."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 426806.0,
      "end_time": 428700.0,
      "text": "And there&#39;s more still."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 428724.0,
      "end_time": 434216.0,
      "text": "A synthetic forest has a significant advantage over a real forest: size."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 434899.0,
      "end_time": 438708.0,
      "text": "This next image that I&#39;m showing you is a map of the Amazon rainforest."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 438732.0,
      "end_time": 444811.0,
      "text": "The Amazon is capable of capturing 1.6 billion tons of CO2 each year."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 444835.0,
      "end_time": 448214.0,
      "text": "This is the equivalent of roughly 25 percent"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 448238.0,
      "end_time": 450533.0,
      "text": "of our annual emissions in the US."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 451700.0,
      "end_time": 453942.0,
      "text": "The land area required for a synthetic forest"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 453966.0,
      "end_time": 456263.0,
      "text": "or a manufactured direct air capture plant"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 456287.0,
      "end_time": 457719.0,
      "text": "to capture the same"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 457743.0,
      "end_time": 459831.0,
      "text": "is 500 times smaller."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 461180.0,
      "end_time": 464227.0,
      "text": "In addition, for a synthetic forest,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 464251.0,
      "end_time": 467116.0,
      "text": "you don&#39;t have to build it on arable land,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 467140.0,
      "end_time": 471411.0,
      "text": "so there&#39;s no competition with farmland or food,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 471435.0,
      "end_time": 476429.0,
      "text": "and there&#39;s also no reason to have to cut down any real trees"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 476453.0,
      "end_time": 477714.0,
      "text": "to do this."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 478570.0,
      "end_time": 480349.0,
      "text": "I want to step back,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 480374.0,
      "end_time": 483940.0,
      "text": "and I want to bring up the concept of negative emissions again."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 484394.0,
      "end_time": 487963.0,
      "text": "Negative emissions require that the CO2 separated"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 487987.0,
      "end_time": 492374.0,
      "text": "be permanently removed from the atmosphere forever,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 492398.0,
      "end_time": 495120.0,
      "text": "which means putting it back underground,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 495144.0,
      "end_time": 497513.0,
      "text": "where it came from in the first place."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 497537.0,
      "end_time": 501750.0,
      "text": "But let&#39;s face it, nobody gets paid to do that today --"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 501100.0,
      "end_time": 502458.0,
      "text": "at least not enough."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 503900.0,
      "end_time": 506497.0,
      "text": "So the companies that are developing these technologies"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 506521.0,
      "end_time": 508998.0,
      "text": "are actually interested in taking the CO2"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 509220.0,
      "end_time": 512169.0,
      "text": "and making something useful out of it, a marketable product."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 512193.0,
      "end_time": 515773.0,
      "text": "It could be liquid fuels, plastics"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 515797.0,
      "end_time": 517543.0,
      "text": "or even synthetic gravel."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 518429.99999999994,
      "end_time": 521208.99999999994,
      "text": "And don&#39;t get me wrong -- these carbon markets are great."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 522549.0,
      "end_time": 525267.0,
      "text": "But I also don&#39;t want you to be disillusioned."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 525292.0,
      "end_time": 529210.0,
      "text": "These are not large enough to solve our climate crisis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 529450.0,
      "end_time": 532877.0,
      "text": "and so what we need to do is we need to actually think about"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 532902.0,
      "end_time": 534379.0,
      "text": "what it could take."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 534403.0,
      "end_time": 538382.0,
      "text": "One thing I&#39;ll absolutely say is positive about the carbon markets"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 538406.0,
      "end_time": 542997.0,
      "text": "is that they allow for new capture plants to be built,"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 543220.0,
      "end_time": 544925.0,
      "text": "and with every capture plant built,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 544949.0,
      "end_time": 546401.0,
      "text": "we learn more."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 546425.0,
      "end_time": 547935.0,
      "text": "And when we learn more,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 547960.0,
      "end_time": 550684.0,
      "text": "we have an opportunity to bring costs down."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 551914.0,
      "end_time": 555441.0,
      "text": "But we also need to be willing to invest"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 555465.0,
      "end_time": 557121.0,
      "text": "as a global society."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 558534.0,
      "end_time": 561908.0,
      "text": "We could have all of the clever thinking and technology in the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 561932.0,
      "end_time": 563567.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s not going to be enough"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 563591.0,
      "end_time": 568470.0,
      "text": "in order for this technology to have a significant impact on climate."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 568494.0,
      "end_time": 570676.0,
      "text": "We really need regulation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 570700.0,
      "end_time": 572233.0,
      "text": "we need subsidies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 572257.0,
      "end_time": 574449.0,
      "text": "taxes on carbon."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 574474.0,
      "end_time": 579284.0,
      "text": "There are a few of us that would absolutely be willing to pay more,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 579308.0,
      "end_time": 581702.0,
      "text": "but what will be required"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 581726.0,
      "end_time": 584419.0,
      "text": "is for carbon-neutral, carbon-negative paths"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 584443.0,
      "end_time": 587132.0,
      "text": "to be affordable for the majority of society"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 587156.0,
      "end_time": 588933.0,
      "text": "in order to impact climate."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 589403.0,
      "end_time": 591976.0,
      "text": "In addition to those kinds of investments,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 592000.0,
      "end_time": 595608.0,
      "text": "we also need investments in research and development."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 595632.0,
      "end_time": 597189.0,
      "text": "So what might that look like?"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 597865.0,
      "end_time": 604145.0,
      "text": "In 1966, the US invested about a half a percent of gross domestic product"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 604169.0,
      "end_time": 605664.0,
      "text": "in the Apollo program."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 606568.0,
      "end_time": 609420.0,
      "text": "It got people safely to the moon"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 609444.0,
      "end_time": 610891.0,
      "text": "and back to the earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 611464.0,
      "end_time": 614993.0,
      "text": "Half a percent of GDP today is about 100 billion dollars."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 615522.0,
      "end_time": 618251.0,
      "text": "So knowing that direct air capture"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 618275.0,
      "end_time": 621478.0,
      "text": "is one front in our fight against climate change,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 621502.0,
      "end_time": 625109.0,
      "text": "imagine that we could invest 20 percent, 20 billion dollars."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 625848.0,
      "end_time": 628728.0,
      "text": "Further, let&#39;s imagine that we could get the costs down"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 628753.0,
      "end_time": 630426.0,
      "text": "to a 100 dollars a ton."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 631274.0,
      "end_time": 635460.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s going to be hard, but it&#39;s part of what makes my job fun."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 635897.0,
      "end_time": 637438.0,
      "text": "And so what does that look like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 637462.0,
      "end_time": 639783.0,
      "text": "20 billion dollars,100 dollars a ton?"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 639807.0,
      "end_time": 642931.0,
      "text": "That requires us to build 200 synthetic forests,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 642955.0,
      "end_time": 648641.0,
      "text": "each capable of capturing a million tons of CO2 per year."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 648665.0,
      "end_time": 652717.0,
      "text": "That adds up to about five percent of US annual emissions."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 653235.0,
      "end_time": 654694.0,
      "text": "It doesn&#39;t sound like much."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 655226.0,
      "end_time": 657340.0,
      "text": "Turns out, it&#39;s actually significant."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 657364.0,
      "end_time": 660818.0,
      "text": "If you look at the emissions associated with long-haul trucking"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 660842.0,
      "end_time": 662574.0,
      "text": "and commercial aircraft,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 662598.0,
      "end_time": 664656.0,
      "text": "they add up to about five percent."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 665458.0,
      "end_time": 669122.0,
      "text": "Our dependence on liquid fuels makes these emissions"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 669147.0,
      "end_time": 671720.0,
      "text": "really difficult to avoid."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 671744.0,
      "end_time": 676559.0,
      "text": "So this investment could absolutely be significant."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 677496.0,
      "end_time": 680598.0,
      "text": "Now, what would it take in terms of land area to do this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 680623.0,
      "end_time": 681961.0,
      "text": "200 plants?"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 682406.0,
      "end_time": 686717.0,
      "text": "It turns out that they would take up about half the land area of Vancouver."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 686741.0,
      "end_time": 688837.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s if they were fueled by natural gas."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 688861.0,
      "end_time": 693533.0,
      "text": "But remember the downside of natural gas -- it also emits CO2."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 693557.0,
      "end_time": 696454.0,
      "text": "So if you use natural gas to do direct air capture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 696478.0,
      "end_time": 700238.0,
      "text": "you only end up capturing about a third of what&#39;s intended,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 700263.0,
      "end_time": 702826.0,
      "text": "unless you have that clever approach of co-capture"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 702850.0,
      "end_time": 704468.0,
      "text": "that Carbon Engineering does."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 705253.0,
      "end_time": 707432.0,
      "text": "And so if we had an alternative approach"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 707456.0,
      "end_time": 710287.0,
      "text": "and used wind or solar to do this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 710311.0,
      "end_time": 713899.0,
      "text": "the land area would be about 15 times larger,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 713923.0,
      "end_time": 715933.0,
      "text": "looking at the state of New Jersey now."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 716360.0,
      "end_time": 719892.0,
      "text": "One of the things that I think about in my work and my research"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 719916.0,
      "end_time": 723841.0,
      "text": "is optimizing and figuring out where we should put these plants"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 723865.0,
      "end_time": 726518.0,
      "text": "and think about the local resources available --"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 726542.0,
      "end_time": 730217.0,
      "text": "whether it&#39;s land, water, cheap and clean electricity --"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 730241.0,
      "end_time": 732943.0,
      "text": "because, for instance, you can use clean electricity"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 732967.0,
      "end_time": 735151.0,
      "text": "to split water to produce hydrogen,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 735176.0,
      "end_time": 739570.0,
      "text": "which is an excellent, carbon-free replacement for natural gas,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 739810.0,
      "end_time": 740831.0,
      "text": "to supply the heat required."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 742212.0,
      "end_time": 745984.0,
      "text": "But I want us to reflect a little bit again on negative emissions."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 746420.0,
      "end_time": 749973.0,
      "text": "Negative emissions should not be considered a silver bullet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 749997.0,
      "end_time": 752500.0,
      "text": "but they may help us if we continue to stall"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 752524.0,
      "end_time": 755783.0,
      "text": "at cutting down on CO2 pollution worldwide."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 756441.0,
      "end_time": 759475.0,
      "text": "But that&#39;s also why we have to be careful."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 759499.0,
      "end_time": 762476.0,
      "text": "This approach is so alluring that it can even be risky,"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 762500.0,
      "end_time": 767474.0,
      "text": "as some may cling onto it as some kind of total solution to our climate crisis."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 767982.0,
      "end_time": 773437.0,
      "text": "It may tempt people to continue to burn fossil fuels 24 hours a day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 773461.0,
      "end_time": 775635.0,
      "text": "365 days a year."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 775659.0,
      "end_time": 778865.0,
      "text": "I argue that we should not see negative emissions"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 778889.0,
      "end_time": 780817.0,
      "text": "as a replacement for stopping pollution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 780841.0,
      "end_time": 786612.0,
      "text": "but rather, as an addition to an existing portfolio that includes everything,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 786636.0,
      "end_time": 788411.0,
      "text": "from increased energy efficiency"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 788435.0,
      "end_time": 790149.0,
      "text": "to low-energy carbon"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 790173.0,
      "end_time": 791806.0,
      "text": "to improved farming --"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 791830.0,
      "end_time": 796831.0,
      "text": "will all collectively get us on a path to net-zero emissions one day."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 797909.0,
      "end_time": 799735.0,
      "text": "A little bit of self-reflection:"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 800481.0,
      "end_time": 802989.0,
      "text": "my husband is an emergency physician."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 803727.0,
      "end_time": 807271.0,
      "text": "And I find myself amazed by the lifesaving work"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 807296.0,
      "end_time": 810593.0,
      "text": "that he and his colleagues do each and every day."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 811235.0,
      "end_time": 815168.0,
      "text": "Yet when I talk to them about my work on carbon capture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 815192.0,
      "end_time": 817454.0,
      "text": "I find that they&#39;re equally amazed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 817896.0,
      "end_time": 822669.0,
      "text": "and that&#39;s because combatting climate change by capturing carbon"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 822693.0,
      "end_time": 824751.0,
      "text": "isn&#39;t just about saving a polar bear"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 824775.0,
      "end_time": 825941.0,
      "text": "or a glacier."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 825965.0,
      "end_time": 827635.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s about saving human lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 829905.0,
      "end_time": 834922.0,
      "text": "A synthetic forest may not ever be as pretty as a real one,"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 834946.0,
      "end_time": 838565.0,
      "text": "but it could just enable us to preserve not only the Amazon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 838589.0,
      "end_time": 840490.0,
      "text": "but all of the people"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 840730.0,
      "end_time": 842443.0,
      "text": "that we love and cherish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 842467.0,
      "end_time": 847129.0,
      "text": "as well as all of our future generations"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 847153.0,
      "end_time": 848815.0,
      "text": "and modern civilization."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 848839.0,
      "end_time": 849992.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 850160.0,
      "end_time": 854238.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}